{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/gastrointestinal-tract-upper-cancers-recognition-referral/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"c01b41ad-4c6c-5422-ace3-35dc70592327","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 548d540f-9603-4b7e-833c-a7f20189877d --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 548d540f-9603-4b7e-833c-a7f20189877d -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item af5ee829-b201-476d-b2b2-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 6fcc626c-2ea3-4a7e-82fb-a7f20189877d --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 6fcc626c-2ea3-4a7e-82fb-a7f20189877d --><!-- begin field 49a6685b-9fe0-40be-85db-a7f20189877d --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 49a6685b-9fe0-40be-85db-a7f20189877d --><!-- begin field f781eec3-ebd2-4bf1-88b2-a7f20189877d --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field f781eec3-ebd2-4bf1-88b2-a7f20189877d --><!-- begin field ab88fabc-e02e-49ac-a3a3-a7f20189877d --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field ab88fabc-e02e-49ac-a3a3-a7f20189877d --><!-- begin field b9bcf056-5000-49b4-9077-a7f20189877d --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field b9bcf056-5000-49b4-9077-a7f20189877d --><!-- begin field 07dbab59-c94d-43ee-ab11-a7f20189877d --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 07dbab59-c94d-43ee-ab11-a7f20189877d --><!-- end item af5ee829-b201-476d-b2b2-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"c0e52ca7-e4e6-57cf-956e-49b2d52e7d08","topicId":"adc668ab-d08a-4b55-8d9a-ca8875f39904","topicName":"Gastrointestinal tract (upper) cancers - recognition and referral","slug":"gastrointestinal-tract-upper-cancers-recognition-referral","lastRevised":"Last revised in February 2021","chapters":[{"id":"a2cfcf1a-dd0a-58de-9d65-a14fa0ad0611","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"a3e084f4-a122-57ce-a6da-caed2683d20d","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"058be16f-48e8-5946-9481-9d3f25e3c6f8","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"f8cfe9e0-9c59-544c-9f31-c2a103f9b4dd","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"fc0a6327-8ba0-5978-8a93-eefed940247e","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"be218b53-cc26-526d-bdfa-7d394e21046f","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"713deae5-bfaa-5c7f-87e0-20e4818e1c17","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"516b9d0a-3400-5ebf-ac16-4c1e2f5a483f","slug":"outcome-me